          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Mercedes-Benz has said before that they would never sell the Mercedes-Benz 300 SLR ‘Uhlenhaut Coupé’, but it appears just that may have happened in a secret auction. The source says the car was auctioned off for charity, and went for a price of 130 million Euros, or $136.8 million dollars. If true, this is easily the most expensive car ever sold at an auction.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
