          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Instead of heading to the race track, it was used as a company car by the head of the test department, Rudolf Uhlenhaut, earning it the nickname “Uhlenhaut Coupe”. Powering the Uhlenhaut Coupe was the fastest road car in the world at the time, with a top speed of 180 mph.",
            "type": "text",
